Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 620
Edition: 1961
Quote: A seller of cheap serge: New Zealand: 1932, Nelson Baylis (private letter); 1941, Sidney J. Baker New Zealand Slang; since ca. 1935, also Australian, as in Baker, 1942; in Australia, too, it bears the derivative sense, `cheap swindler' (Baker, 1945).
